    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "Tires must be stored in a cool, dry and dark room with adequate ventilation. Tires must never come into contact with fuel, oil, grease or chemicals. Do not store summer tires in storage areas with ambient temperatures of less than 5° F (–15° C).<br/>Complete wheels can be stacked for storage; we recommend that you increase the tire pressure by approx. 6 psi (0.4 bar).<br/>If the tires are not mounted on wheels, it is best to store them in a vertical position. We recommend that you turn tires stored in this position every two weeks in order to prevent flat spots. Tires that are stacked in a horizontal position will become severely deformed and cannot be seated properly in the rim flange when they are mounted."
    
    }
    
    }
    
    ]
    
    }
    
